## End-to-End Smoke Test

The final smoke test validates the complete request path:

```
Browser/curl --> Cloudflare DNS --> Cloudflare Proxy --> VPS:443 --> Caddy --> Response
```

```bash
# From local machine:
# 1. DNS resolves
dig +short A platform.yourdomain.dev
# Expected: Cloudflare IPs

# 2. HTTPS request reaches Caddy
curl -v https://platform.yourdomain.dev 2>&1
# Expected: TLS handshake succeeds, response from Caddy
# Response body: "Service not found" (503) or Caddy default
# (dashboard is not deployed yet, so 503 from the catch-all is correct)

# 3. Wildcard subdomain also works
curl -v https://test.yourdomain.dev 2>&1
# Expected: 503 "Service not found" (Caddy catch-all)
```

---

## Expected State After Completion

All 33 tests in the matrix pass. The infrastructure is ready for Phase 2 (database migrations) and all subsequent phases.

Specifically:
1. Terraform state is clean
2. VPS is healthy and secure
3. VPS can reach all AWS services (RDS, S3, Secrets Manager)
4. Caddy is serving and its admin API is functional
5. DNS resolves all subdomains through Cloudflare
6. TLS works end-to-end
7. No unauthorized access points exist

---

## If Tests Fail

| Failure Category | Fix In |
|-----------------|--------|
| AWS resource missing | Step 1 (re-run `terraform apply`) |
| VPS system issue | Step 2 (re-run provisioning script) |
| AWS connectivity from VPS | Step 1 (check IAM) or Step 2 (check AWS CLI config) |
| RDS connectivity | Step 1 (check security group) + Step 2 (check VPS IP in SG) |
| Caddy issue | Step 3 (check config, service, plugin) |
| DNS issue | Step 4 (check Cloudflare records) |
| TLS issue | Step 3 (Caddy cert) + Step 4 (Cloudflare SSL mode) |
| Security issue | Step 2 (SSH, firewall) or Step 3 (Caddy admin API binding) |

After fixing, re-run `verify-infrastructure.sh` and `verify-dns.sh`.
